Hi [~chris.douglas],
Thanks for your jumping in,
bq. Does this occur when the absolute guaranteed capacity of a queue is smaller than the minimum container size?
This can be happened when 
(used_capacity_of_a_queue + newly_allocated_container_resource > guaranteed_resource_of_a_queue) && (used_capacity_of_a_queue < guaranteed_resource_of_a_queue),
So I propose to change
{code}
while (toBePreempt > 0):
  foreach application:
    foreach container:
      if (toBePreempt > 0):
        do preemption
{code}
To
{code}
while (toBePreempt > 0):
  foreach application:
    foreach container:
      if (toBePreempt > 0) and (container.resource < toBePreempt * 2):
        do preemption
{code}
To make sure a container is not preempted too aggressive. 
Does this answered your question?

Thanks,
Wangda

